    "## 1. Dataset at a Glance\n",
    "\n",
    "Before touching `.describe()`, let's decode the column names. These aren't arbitrary labels - each one is a clinical measurement with a specific medical interpretaion:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Feature | Clinical Meaning | Type |\n",
    "|---------| -----------------|------|\n",
    "| Age | Patient age in years | Numeric |\n",
    "| Chest pain type | 1=Typical anginam, 2=Atypical angina, 3=Non-anginal, 4=Asymtomatic | Ordinal |\n",
    "| BP | Resting blood pressure (mmHg) | Numeric |\n",
    "| Cholesterol | Serum cholesterol (mg/dL) | Numeric |\n",
    "| FBS over 120 | Fasting blood sugar > 120 mg/dL: 1=True, 0=False | Binary |\n",
    "| EKG results | 0=Normal, 1=ST-T wave abnormality, 2=Left ventricular hypertrophy | Ordinal|\n",
    "| Max HR | Maximum heart rate achieved during exercise stress test | Numeric |\n",
    "| Exercise angina | Chest pain induced by exercise: 1=Yes, 0=No | Binary |\n",
    "| ST depression | Depression of ST segment relative to rest (exercise ECG) | Numeric |\n",
    "| Slope of ST | Slope of peak exercise ST segment: 1=Unsloping, 2=Flat, 3=Downsloping | Ordinal |\n",
    "| Number of vessels fluro | Major vessels colored by fluoroscopy (0-3) - not: \"fluro\" is the dataset's spelling | Ordinal|\n",
    "| Thallium | Nuclear stress test: 3=Normal, 6=Fixed defect, 7=Reversible defect | Ordinal |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Clinical note:** Chest pain type 4 (asymptomatic) is counter-intuitively the\n",
    "> highest-risk group - silent ischemia is more dangerous precisely because patients\n",
    "> don't seek help.\n"
   ]
