     "status": "completed"
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Not all missing value stretegies are equal. We compare three approaches: \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Mean/Median imputation**: Fast, interpretable. Assumes data is Missing Completely At Random (MCAR). Distorts distributions slightly.\n",
    "- **KNN imputation**: Uses patient similarity to fill gaps. Clinically intuitive - \"fill in what similar patients had\". Better for MAR data, more compute-intensive.\n",
    "- **Flag-then-fill**: Adds a binary `_was_missing` column before imputing. Preserves the *information* that a value was missing - which tree models can exploit directly."
   ]
  },
